div.p: GOAL Digital Academy is proud and committed to supporting you and your family during this time of need.Our mission from thebeginning hasbeen to support, encourage and educate yourstudent.We want all of our seniors, the GOAL Digital Academy Class of 2020 to have a proper senior celebration.The senior luncheon has been rescheduled forMay 7, 2020, starting at 10:00am.If we are unable to hold an in-person luncheon on May 7th, we will schedule individual online senior meetings with your counselor.The luncheon and/or online guidance senior meeting will count for all of your exam grades for your final semester of high school.

The GOAL Digital Academy Graduation will take place on Friday, May 22, 2020, at 6:30pm.If we cannot hold a graduation ceremony in person, the ceremonywill be held virtually. Approximately, 130 diplomas are expected to be awarded!Our staff, including myself, are so proud of everything that you have accomplished, especially how you have stepped up and remained strong during this unique time in our history.While we are not able to see each other and your families in person, we want to recognize your achievements virtually with your families and friends.

If the May ceremony cannot be held in person,GOAL Digital Academy will host a graduation ceremony on Wednesday, August 19, 2020. The ceremony will be held at the Mid-Ohio Conference Center/GOAL Mansfield Lab located at 890 West Fourth Street Mansfield, Ohio 44906 starting at 6:30pm.

Please share the dates for your senior luncheon and graduation with your family, friends and classmates.Stay home, keep positive, healthy and safe.Please know that everyone at GOAL is thinking of you and we will continue to support you in every possible way.

p.span:
The students, staff, and administration of GOAL Digital Academy welcome you to our website. We are confident that you will find the information on this site useful and that you will learn more about what makes GOAL Digital Academy a special place.
GOAL Digital Academy has a dedicated and experienced staff, who provide not only standard curriculum, but also credit flexibility, dropout prevention, and credit recovery programs for high school students. We also offer open labs with certified teachers as tutors, blended learning courses and resource rooms for students.
GOAL Digital Academy is committed to providing a safe, caring, and challenging educational environment that promotes learning and achievement for all students. We recognize and celebrate diverse learning styles, interests, talents, and uniqueness of our students and strive to offer a rich variety of meaningful learning experiences that will inspire innovative thinkers and confident learners.
GOAL Digital Academy opened its program in the2002-2003school year.

span.span: GOAL Digital Academy has expanded to sevenlocations:
Mansfield, Galion, Delaware, Marion, Cardington, Mt. Vernon & Newark.
We are an online school with approximately 700 students ranging from1st grade through high school.
We have a diverse instructor team trained in rich learning styles.
